TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {11293=USDJPY – Retail forex trading crowds remain aggressively long the US Dollar (ticker: USDOLLAR) versus the Japanese Yen, but we believe that a significant shift in positioning confirms that the USDJPY set a significant bottom through September., 9820=The majority of retail traders first turned short the British Pound in August as the pair crossed above the $1.56 mark in August—giving us a fairly consistent bullish contrarian bias. Yet total long interest surged 59 percent from last week, while shorts dropped a similar 39 percent. Our SSI data shows that a mere 51% of traders are currently short GBPUSD versus 73% last week., 8020=Retail trading crowds had previously remained short Euros as it crossed above the $1.25 mark in mid-September, and the fact that they have now flipped in their net trading bias is further confirmation that we may have set a significant EURUSD top.}
